  "body": " **Description**\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: ...\r\n1.  Open Status app.\r\n2. Click on Recover access option.\r\n3. After that screen will appear as shown in attached screenshot.\r\n![screenshot_2017-12-06-17-54-30-465_im status ethereum](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20433356/33663477-2b26de00-dab6-11e7-9e22-56eef1f74743.png)\r\n4. Click on Recover Access option once again. It opens another new account instead of recovering an old one.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nI feel instead of creating new account, it should recover the previous one which already created & UserName for that account this option if there on UI, so that will get to know, for which account getting recovered if multiple accounts are there on one device.\r\n& While creating new account it's not validating  password length & Pass phrase 12 words.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nGetting created each time new account.\r\nNot validating password length.\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: ... 0.9.12\r\n* Operating System: Android 6.0.1\r\n\r\n",
